  "response": "# Portfolio Strategy for Balancing Innovation and Maintenance\n\n## Core Framework\n\n### 1. Resource Allocation Model (70-20-10)\n- **70%**: Core system maintenance, stability, and incremental improvements\n- **20%**: Adjacent innovations (moderate risk, building on existing capabilities)\n- **10%**: Transformational innovations (high-risk, high-reward initiatives)\n\n### 2. Governance Structure\n- **Dual-track management system** with separate but coordinated processes for maintenance and innovation\n- **Quarterly portfolio reviews** to assess balance and adjust allocations\n- **Cross-functional investment board** with representation from technology, business, and finance\n\n### 3. Evaluation Criteria\n\n#### Maintenance Initiatives\n- System reliability metrics (uptime, performance)\n- Technical debt reduction\n- Security compliance\n- Cost efficiency improvements\n\n#### Innovation Initiatives\n- Strategic alignment score\n- Market opportunity size\n- Technical feasibility assessment\n- Time-to-value projection\n\n### 4. Risk Management\n- **Stage-gate process** for innovation projects with clear go/no-go decision points\n- **Innovation sandbox environments** isolated from production systems\n- **Failure budget** allocation for experimental initiatives\n\n### 5. Talent Allocation\n- Rotational program between maintenance and innovation teams\n- Dedicated innovation time for maintenance team members (e.g., 10% time)\n- Skills development program to build capabilities in both domains\n\n## Implementation Approach\n\n1. Baseline current portfolio allocation and performance\n2. Establish governance mechanisms and decision frameworks\n3. Develop balanced scorecard for tracking portfolio health\n4. Implement regular review cycles with clear adjustment protocols\n5. Create feedback loops between innovation and maintenance teams",
